The paper discusses a reinforcement learning approach with a focus on visual domains, which suggests a likely fit with the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of subgoals and options in the approach also suggests a potential fit with robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper specifically mentions testing the approach on games from the Atari suite, which suggests a potential fit with computer vision (cs.CV).
